				<main><article class="main-content"><h1 class="">News and Events at Riverside</h1>
        <p class="">Be sure to check out our News &amp; Events page for current activities and information about our district and our schools. We'll update this page frequently to keep you informed about the latest happenings here at Riverside!</p>
        
        <div class="pom-container">
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="schoolclosuresextendedtoendofschoolyear"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">School Closures Extended to End of School Year</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">March 30, 2020</p></div>
<p class="">In collaboration with Governor Ducey, Superintendent Hoffman of the Arizona Department of Education, and the Centers for Disease Control, the Riverside Elementary School District No. 2 will be closing its schools for the remainder of the 2019–2020 school year. This decision is to ensure the health and safety of our students, faculty, and staff. For more information, please see our <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/March-30-2020-RESD-Parent-Notification-School-Closure-To-End-Of-School-Year.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">parent notification</a>.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">30 de marzo, 2020</p></div>
<p></p>
<p class="">En colaboración con el gobernador Ducey, el superintendente Hoffman del Departamento de Educación de Arizona y los Centros para el Control de Enfermedades, el Distrito Escolar Riverside No. 2 cerrará sus escuelas por el resto del año escolar 2019–2020. Esta decisión es para asegurar la salud y seguridad de nuestros estudiantes, maestros y personal. Para obtener más información, consulte nuestra <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/March-30-2020-RESD-Parent-Notification-School-Closure-To-End-Of-School-Year-Spanish.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">notificación para padres</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="extendedschoolclosures"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Extended School Closures</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class=""></p>
<p class="">Dear Parents and Guardians, </p>
<p></p>
<p class="">In order for us to ensure the safety and health of our students our school will remain closed until further notice. These are challenging times for us all. The Riverside students and community are resilient and we will prevail together. </p>
<p class="">We will continue coordinating with the Governor, Department of Health, CDC and the Arizona Department of Education to determine the duration of our school closure regarding when it will be safe for our students to return to school.</p>
<p class="">Please <a href="/Home" title="" alt="" target="_self">continue checking our website</a>. Our principals will be adding work packets for students to complete during the closure. We will also be <a href="https://www.facebook.com/RiversideSchools/" title="" alt="" target="_blank">posting updates on our Facebook page</a>. Thank you for your support during this difficult time. Please <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/RESD-Parent-Letter-to-Extend-School-Closures-English-and-Spanish.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank" class="">read the entire letter in both English and Spanish from Superintendent Rivera</a>.</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="mealsonwheels"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Meals on Wheels</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">Starting March 25, 2020, and until further notice, we will provide free student breakfast and lunch via meals on wheels. Meals on wheels ensures all students can eat! For details, please see our meals on wheels flyer.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><ul class="">
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/March-24-2020-Meals-On-Wheels-Flyer.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">Meals on Wheels Flyer</a></li>
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/March-24-2020-Meals-On-Wheels-Flyer-Spanish.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">Meals on Wheels Flyer - Spanish</a></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="schoolclosure"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">School Closure</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">Dear parents and guardians,</p>
<p class="">We are in a time of crisis where we need to be very cautious for the sake of our students, staff, and community member’s safety and health. Many of you are aware of the pandemic caused by the coronavirus (COVID-19). With the safety and health of our students in mind, Riverside Traditional, Kings Ridge Preparatory, and MIT Junior High School will be closed <strong>until further notice</strong>. For more information, please <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/Parent-Closure-Letter.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">read the entire parent closure letter</a>. This <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Documents/Parent-Closure-Letter-Spanish.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">letter is also available in Spanish</a>.</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="mealsduringclosure"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Meals During Closure</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="" lang="es">
<p class="">Riverside Elementary School District No. 2 will be offering free meals to all students ages 18 and younger during school closure. Starting March 16, 2020, and until further notice. </p>
<p class="">Breakfast and lunch will be available at Riverside Traditional School, Kings Ridge Preparatory Academy, MIT STEM Jr. High, and MIT High School. Students are not required to go to their assigned school for meals, they may go to any of the schools within our district. Meals will be available between 10:00 and 11:00 a.m. Each child will receive two pre-packaged meals per day (breakfast and lunch).</p>
<p class="">El Distrito Escolar Riverside No. 2 ofrecerá comidas gratis a todas las edades de 18 años y menores durante el cierre de la escuela. A partir del 16 de marzo de 2020 y hasta nuevo aviso.</p>
<p class="">El desayuno y el almuerzo estarán disponibles en Riverside Traditional School, Kings Ridge Preparatory Academy, MIT STEM Jr. High y MIT High School. Los estudiantes no están obligados a ir a la escuela asignada para las comidas, pueden ir a cualquiera de las escuelas de nuestro distrito. Las comidas estarán disponibles entre las 10:00 a.m. y las 11:00 a.m. Cada niño recibirá 2 comidas preenvasadas por día (desayuno y almuerzo).</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="census"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Census</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<div class=""><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1e8vbVrfqzaFJpPIjlC7gwPt163I_hMHp" title="" alt="" target="_blank"><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_345659/site_345660/Graphics/photonews_census_040820.jpg" alt="View the census flyer" class="float-right" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px; margin-right: 1em; display: block;"></a></div>
<p class="">Census results help determine how billions of dollars in federal funding flow into states and communities each year. The results determine how many seats in congress each state gets. It's mandated by the U.S. Constitution in Article 1, Section 2: The U.S. has counted its population every 10 years since 1790. </p>
<p class="">Your answers to the census are anonymous when you respond. This information will be to produce statistics only. The U.S. Census Bureau is bound by law to protect your answers and keep them strictly confidential. The law ensures that any government agency or court can not hold your information against you and is never published. Be sure to do your part in participating by visiting the <a href="https://www.2020census.gov/" title="" alt="" target="_blank">2020 Census website.</a></p>
<div class="pom-container clearfix"></div>
</div></div>
</div>
</div>
